(49, '1.56 PROG MC UV400', '', '300', 100, 'product-featured-49.jpg', '<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;mso-add-space:auto;\r\nline-height:normal\"><b><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt\">What are Progressive\r\nlenses?<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;mso-add-space:\r\nauto;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:normal;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]-->-<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">       \r\n</span><!--[endif]-->Progressive lenses combines your distance and\r\nreading prescriptions seamlessly into one lens. They allow you to see near, far\r\nand everything in between.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;mso-add-space:\r\nauto;line-height:normal\"><o:p> </o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;mso-add-space:\r\nauto;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:normal;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]-->-<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">       \r\n</span><!--[endif]-->A pair of progressives is probably be enough to\r\nmeet most of your vision needs.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\"><o:p> </o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\"><b><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;\r\nline-height:107%\">Do I need Progressive lenses?<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;mso-add-space:\r\nauto;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:normal;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]-->-<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">       \r\n</span><!--[endif]-->Progressive lenses are generally fitted for\r\npeople aged 40 years old and above who have difficulty seeing things clearly at\r\ntheir usual reading distances. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;mso-add-space:\r\nauto;line-height:normal\"><o:p> </o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;mso-add-space:\r\nauto;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:normal;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]-->-<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">       \r\n</span><!--[endif]-->If you noticed that you are holding your reading\r\nmaterial further away to see clearly; or if you are short-sighted and start\r\nremoving your glasses to see clearer. <o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;mso-add-space:\r\nauto;line-height:normal\"><o:p> </o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;mso-add-space:\r\nauto;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:normal;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]-->-<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">       \r\n</span><!--[endif]-->These are signs that you may require a reading\r\nprescription, and this is where progressive lenses come in.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\"><o:p> </o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\"><b><span style=\"font-size:14.0pt;\r\nline-height:107%\">How do Progressive lenses work?<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;mso-add-space:\r\nauto;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:normal;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]-->-<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">       \r\n</span><!--[endif]-->Progressive lenses work by changing the power\r\nfrom the top of the lens to the bottom gradually. You can enjoy a clear range\r\nof vision over various distances by simply moving your eyes up and down to\r\ncater to your visual activity.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;mso-add-space:\r\nauto;line-height:normal\"><o:p> </o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;mso-add-space:\r\nauto;text-indent:-18.0pt;line-height:normal;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1\"><!--[if !supportLists]-->-<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: \" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";\"=\"\">       \r\n</span><!--[endif]-->The top portion of the lens will be for distance\r\nvision, and the bottom portion will be for near work. The portion in between is\r\nused for intermediate distances such as the computer screen.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;mso-add-space:auto;\r\nline-height:normal\"><o:p> </o:p></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;line-height:107%;font-family:\" calibri\",sans-serif;=\"\" mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:dengxian;mso-fareast-theme-font:=\"\" minor-fareast;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-bidi-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";=\"\" mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;mso-ansi-language:en-my;mso-fareast-language:=\"\" zh-cn;mso-bidi-language:ar-sa\"=\"\">Unlike the bifocal lenses in the past,\r\nprogressive lenses do not have the distinct line in the middle.</span><br></p>', 'SPH +2.00 ~ -2.00 / CYL -PL ~ -2.00 / ADD +1.00 ~ +2.00', '<p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Roboto;color:#333333\">UV400\r\nmeans one hundred percent anti-ultraviolet.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Roboto;color:#333333\"> </span></p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Roboto;color:#333333\">UV\r\nis the wavelength of 200nm ~ 380nm from the sun light, including three\r\ncategories: UVA wavelength of 315nm ~ 380nm, UVB wavelength of 280nm ~ 315nm,\r\nUVC wavelength of 200nm ~ 280nm. <o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Roboto;color:#333333\"> </span></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;font-family:Roboto;color:#333333\">UV-400:\r\nOptical lens with \"UV-400\"  can block all the UV, can be 100%\r\nreflection, absorption of ultraviolet light.<o:p></o:p></span></p>', '', '', 14, 1, 1, 9, '123'),
(50, '1.56 PROG MC UV420', '', '350', 100, 'product-featured-50.jpg', '<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 700;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14pt;\">What are Progressive lenses?<o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></o:p></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Progressive lenses combines your distance and reading prescriptions seamlessly into one lens. They allow you to see near, far and everything in between.<o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\"><o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>A pair of progressives is probably be enough to meet most of your vision needs.</p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\"><br style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\"><br style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 700;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14pt; line-height: 19.9733px;\">Do I need Progressive lenses?<o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></o:p></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Progressive lenses are generally fitted for people aged 40 years old and above who have difficulty seeing things clearly at their usual reading distances.<o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\"><o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>If you noticed that you are holding your reading material further away to see clearly; or if you are short-sighted and start removing your glasses to see clearer.<o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\"><o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>These are signs that you may require a reading prescription, and this is where progressive lenses come in.</p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\"><br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\"><br></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 700;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14pt; line-height: 19.9733px;\">How do Progressive lenses work?<o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></o:p></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Progressive lenses work by changing the power from the top of the lens to the bottom gradually. You can enjoy a clear range of vision over various distances by simply moving your eyes up and down to cater to your visual activity.<o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\"><o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>The top portion of the lens will be for distance vision, and the bottom portion will be for near work. The portion in between is used for intermediate distances such as the computer screen.<o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\"><o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">&nbsp;</o:p></p><p style=\"padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">Unlike the bifocal lenses in the past, progressive lenses do not have the distinct line in the middle.</span></p>', 'SPH +2.00 ~ -2.00 / CYL -PL ~ -2.00 / ADD +1.00 ~ +3.00', '<p style=\"margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:7.5pt;margin-left:0cm\">●\r\nThis is a very convenient type of lens that allows the wearer to focus on\r\nobjects both at close range and&nbsp; far range through a single lens.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p style=\"margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:7.5pt;margin-left:0cm\">●\r\nThis type of lens is designed to enable&nbsp; viewing of objects in the&nbsp;\r\ndistance, at&nbsp; close range and in the&nbsp; intermediate&nbsp; distance\r\nwith&nbsp; corresponding changes in&nbsp; power&nbsp; for each distance.<o:p></o:p></p><p style=\"margin:0cm\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p style=\"margin:0cm\">● BLUE BOLCK was added to the lenses. because the most\r\ncommon effects of excessive exposure to blue light are eye fatigue, blurred vision\r\nand headaches. However, recent studies have focused on the negative effects of\r\nblue light on circadian rhythms and have found that watching TV or using a\r\ntablet before bedtime, for example, can lead to irritability and interrupted\r\nsleep cycles. In extreme cases, too much blue light exposure can even lead to\r\npermanent eye damage and vision loss.<o:p></o:p></p>', '', '', 3, 1, 1, 10, '7777');
