(68, '1.56 UV400 PROGRESSIVE', '', '600', 100, 'product-featured-68.jpg', '<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt;\">What are Progressive lenses?<o:p></o:p></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Progressive lenses combines your distance and reading prescriptions seamlessly into one lens. They allow you to see near, far and everything in between.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: normal;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>A pair of progressives is probably be enough to meet most of your vision needs.</p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\"><o:p><br></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\"><o:p><br></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 19.9733px;\">Do I need Progressive lenses?<o:p></o:p></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Progressive lenses are generally fitted for people aged 40 years old and above who have difficulty seeing things clearly at their usual reading distances.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: normal;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>If you noticed that you are holding your reading material further away to see clearly; or if you are short-sighted and start removing your glasses to see clearer.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: normal;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>These are signs that you may require a reading prescription, and this is where progressive lenses come in.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\"><span style=\"font-weight: 700;\"><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; line-height: 19.9733px;\">How do Progressive lenses work?<o:p></o:p></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Progressive lenses work by changing the power from the top of the lens to the bottom gradually. You can enjoy a clear range of vision over various distances by simply moving your eyes up and down to cater to your visual activity.<o:p></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: normal;\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>The top portion of the lens will be for distance vision, and the bottom portion will be for near work. The portion in between is used for intermediate distances suc