 padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>If you noticed that you are holding your reading material further away to see clearly; or if you are short-sighted and start removing your glasses to see clearer.<o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\"><o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>These are signs that you may require a reading prescription, and this is where progressive lenses come in.<o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px;\"><o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 700;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14pt; line-height: 19.9733px;\">How do Progressive lenses work?<o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></o:p></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Progressive lenses work by changing the power from the top of the lens to the bottom gradually. You can enjoy a clear range of vision over various distances by simply moving your eyes up and down to cater to your visual activity.<o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\"><o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>The top portion of the lens will be for distance vision, and the bottom portion will be for near work. The portion in between is used for intermediate distances such as the computer screen.<o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\"><o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">&nbsp;</o:p></p><p style=\"padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\">Unlike the bifocal lenses in the past, progressive lenses do not have the distinct line in the middle.</span></p><p style=\"padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 11pt; line-height: 15.6933px; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;\"><br></span></p>', 'SPH +6.00 ~ 6.00 / CYL -PL ~ -4.00 / ADD +1.00 ~ +3.00', '<p style=\"margin-top:0cm;margin-right:0cm;margin-bottom:7.5pt;margin-left:0cm\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Roboto; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">1.\r\nDRIVING AT NIGHT IS NOT THE SAME</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Roboto;\"><o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Roboto;\">Lights\r\ncreate more reflections and glare on our glasses at night. On the road, they\r\ncan come from all directions and common sources like headlights, traffic lights,\r\nand street lamps.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Roboto;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Roboto;\">Especially\r\nwhen you\'re driving at night, the additional reflections and glare can impact\r\nyour vision and create discomfort.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Roboto;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Roboto;\">2.\r\nTHE EVERYDAY LENS FOR EVERY DRIVER<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Roboto;\">Whether\r\nyou\'re a professional, casual or family driver, once night falls, you face the\r\nsame distracting halos. Crizal drive lenses are specially designed to help you\r\nsee clearly for a smoother ride day and night.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Roboto;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Roboto;\">3.FULL\r\nCONFIDENCE ​EVEN AT NIGHT<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Roboto;\">Optimised\r\nfor night driving, Crizal drive lenses have up to 90% less reflection(3)\r\ncompared to ordinary lenses. This minimises the dangerous reflections from\r\nsurrounding lights, so you can drive safely and confidently in low light.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Roboto;\">&nbsp;</span></p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Roboto;\">4.SUPERIOR\r\nCLEAR VISION IN THE DAY<o:p></o:p></span></p><p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n</p><p style=\"margin: 0cm 0cm 7.5pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt; font-family: Roboto;\">Benefit\r\nfrom wearing Crizal drive lenses in the day as well. They ensure confidence and\r\ncomfort by maintaining clear and sharp vision all day long, in addition to\r\nenhancing your night vision.<o:p></o:p></span></p>', '', '', 0, 1, 1, 43, '255'),
