(152, '1.67 DRIVE Polcarbonate PROGRESSIVE', '', '900', 100, 'product-featured-152.jpg', '<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 700;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14pt;\">What are Progressive lenses?<o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></o:p></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Progressive lenses combines your distance and reading prescriptions seamlessly into one lens. They allow you to see near, far and everything in between.<o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\"><o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>A pair of progressives is probably be enough to meet most of your vision needs.</p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\"><o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><br style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\"><o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"><br style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-weight: 700;\"><span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14pt; line-height: 19.9733px;\">Do I need Progressive lenses?<o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></o:p></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Progressive lenses are generally fitted for people aged 40 years old and above who have difficulty seeing things clearly at their usual reading distances.<o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\"><o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm;