rgin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 14pt; line-height: 19.9733px;\">How do Progressive lenses work?<o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></o:p></span></span></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>Progressive lenses work by changing the power from the top of the lens to the bottom gradually. You can enjoy a clear range of vision over various distances by simply moving your eyes up and down to cater to your visual activity.<o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\"></o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; line-height: normal;\"><o:p style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">&nbsp;</o:p></p><p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0cm; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-size: 14px; text-indent: -18pt; line-height: normal;\">-<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>The top portion of the lens will be for distance vision, and the bottom portion will be for near work. The portion in between is used for intermediate distances such as the computer screen.<o:p style=\"ma